## Observation

After performing this lab, it was observed that static members are useful for storing common data shared by all objects. Const member functions help protect object data from accidental modification. It was also observed that const objects can only call const functions.

Friend functions were useful when private data from two different classes had to be accessed. Const reference helped pass objects to functions safely without unnecessary copying.

