## Discussion

This lab helped to understand how advanced class features make C++ programs more secure and organized. Static members are useful when a value must be shared among all objects. Const functions are important when the function should only read data and not modify it.

Friend functions should be used carefully because they can access private data of a class. However, they are useful when two classes need to share private data for a common operation. Overall, these concepts improve program design and prepare the foundation for more advanced object-oriented programming.

